        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 5:54PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 554 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hanover, or 21 miles north of Pueblo Airport, moving east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fountain, Hanover, and Security-Widefield.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 700 PM MDT for
southeastern and east central Colorado.</instruction>
